<inglise> Council Directive 70/373/EEC of 20 July 1970 on the introduction of Community methods of sampling and analysis for the official control of feeding-stuffs </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 70/373/EM&Uuml; s&ouml;&ouml;da ametlikuks kontrolliks vajalike &uuml;henduse prooviv&otilde;tu- ja anal&uuml;&uuml;simeetodite kehtestamise kohta 20. juuli 1970 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa &uuml;henduste n&otilde;ukogu, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Articles 43 and 100 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikleid 43 ja 100, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the Economic and Social Committee; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the production, marketing and use of feeding-stuffs occupy an extremely important place in the European Economic Community; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: s&ouml;&ouml;da tootmisel, turustamisel ja kasutamisel on &auml;&auml;rmiselt oluline koht Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas animal production in agriculture depends to a large extent on the use of appropriate good quality feeding-stuffs; </inglise>
<eesti> p&otilde;llumajanduses s&otilde;ltub loomakasvatustoodang olulisel m&auml;&auml;ral sobivate kvaliteetsete s&ouml;&ouml;tade kasutamisest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the existence of rules concerning feeding-stuffs is essential to an increase in agricultural productivity; </inglise>
<eesti> s&ouml;&ouml;tasid k&auml;sitlevate eeskirjade olemasolu on oluline p&otilde;llumajanduse tootlikkuse suurendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the introduction of Community measures concerning the quality and composition of feeding-stuffs used in the European Economic Community makes it necessary to establish uniform methods of sampling and analysis to be used by the authorities of the Member States for carrying out official controls; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;henduse meetmete v&otilde;tmise t&otilde;ttu Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduses kasutatud s&ouml;&ouml;tade kvaliteedi ja koostise suhtes on vaja kehtestada &uuml;htsed prooviv&otilde;tu- ja anal&uuml;&uuml;simeetodid, mida liikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused kasutaksid ametlike kontrollide tegemisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, furthermore, the methods of sampling and analysis used for checking compliance with those national standards remaining in force must be the same throughout the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> lisaks peavad kontrolliks kasutatavad prooviv&otilde;tu- ja anal&uuml;&uuml;simeetodid, mis on koosk&otilde;las kehtima j&auml;&auml;vate riiklike standarditega, olema &uuml;henduse k&otilde;igis osades samad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas certain Member States are already applying official methods of sampling and analysis and these differ to some extent as regards their basic principles; whereas these methods directly affect the establishment and functioning of the common market and should therefore be harmonised; </inglise>
<eesti> m&otilde;ned liikmesriigid rakendavad juba ametlikke prooviv&otilde;tu- ja anal&uuml;&uuml;simeetodeid ning need erinevad &uuml;ksteisest osaliselt p&otilde;him&otilde;tete poolest; k&otilde;nealused meetodid m&otilde;jutavad otseselt &uuml;histuru kujunemist ja toimimist ning tuleks seet&otilde;ttu &uuml;htlustada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the establishment of uniform methods is purely an implementing measure of a technical and scientific nature; whereas a rapid procedure is needed to develop, improve and amplify those methods; whereas, in order to facilitate the adoption of these measures, a procedure should be provided for establishing close co-operation between Member States and the Commission within a Standing Committee for Feeding-stuffs; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;htsete meetodite sisseseadmine on vaid tehnilist ja teaduslikku laadi rakendusmeede; k&otilde;nealuste meetodite arendamiseks, parandamiseks ja t&otilde;hustamiseks on vaja kiiret menetlust; k&otilde;nealuste meetmete vastuv&otilde;tmise h&otilde;lbustamiseks tuleks ette n&auml;ha menetlus, millega luuakse liikmesriikide ja komisjoni vahel tihe koost&ouml;&ouml; alalise s&ouml;&ouml;dakomitee raames; </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States shall take all measures necessary to ensure that official controls of feeding-stuffs, for the purpose of checking compliance with requirements arising under provisions laid down by law, regulation or administrative action concerning the quality and composition of feeding-stuffs, are carried out using the Community methods of sampling and analysis to be established in the directives referred to in Article 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed kindlustamaks, et s&ouml;&ouml;tade kvaliteeti ja koostist reguleerivate &otilde;igusnormide n&otilde;uetele vastavuse ametlik kontroll tehakse artiklis 2 osutatud direktiivide kohaselt kehtestatud &uuml;henduse prooviv&otilde;tu- ja anal&uuml;&uuml;simeetodite abil. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The methods referred to in Article 1 shall be established by directive and in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 3, account being taken of current scientific and technical knowledge and of proven methods. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 1 osutatud meetodid kehtestatakse direktiiviga artiklis 3 s&auml;testatud korras, v&otilde;ttes arvesse teaduslike ja tehniliste teadmiste praegust taset ja tunnustatud meetodeid. </eesti>
<inglise> These directives shall set appropriate time limits for incorporating those methods in national provisions. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende direktiividega kehtestatakse asjakohased ajalised piirangud k&otilde;nealuste meetmete inkorporeerimiseks siseriiklikesse &otilde;igusnormidesse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the procedure laid down in this Article is to be followed, matters shall be referred by the Chairman, either on his own initiative or at the request of the representative of a Member State, to the Standing Committee for Feeding-stuffs (hereinafter called the "Committee") set up by the Council Decision of 20 July 19701. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas artiklis etten&auml;htud korra kohaselt suunab eesistuja kas omal algatusel v&otilde;i liikmesriigi esindaja taotlusel asjakohased k&uuml;simused n&otilde;ukogu 20. juuli 1970. aasta otsusega (1) asutatud alalisele s&ouml;&ouml;dakomiteele (edaspidi "komitee"). </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The representative of the Commission shall submit to the Committee a draft of the measures to be adopted. </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;etavate meetmete eeln&otilde;u esitab komiteele komisjoni esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall deliver its Opinion on the draft within a time limit set by he Chairman according to the urgency of the matter. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee esitab oma arvamuse eeln&otilde;u kohta aja jooksul, mille m&auml;&auml;rab esimees vastavalt k&uuml;simuse kiireloomulisusele. </eesti>
<inglise> Opinions shall be delivered by a majority of twelve votes, the votes of the Member States being weighted as provided in Article 148 (2) of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvamused v&otilde;etakse vastu kaheteistk&uuml;mne poolth&auml;&auml;lega, liikmesriikide h&auml;&auml;li arvestatakse asutamislepingu artikli 148 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> The Chairman shall not vote. </inglise>
<eesti> Eesistuja ei h&auml;&auml;leta. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. (a) The Commission shall adopt the measures envisaged where they are in accordance with the Opinion of the Committee. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. a) Kui kavandatavad meetmed on komitee arvamusega koosk&otilde;las, v&otilde;tab komisjon need vastu. </eesti>
<inglise> (b) Where the measures envisaged are not in accordance with the Opinion of the Committee, or if no Opinion is delivered, the Commission shall without delay propose to the Council the measures to be adopted. </inglise>
<eesti> b) Kui kavandatavad meetmed ei ole komitee arvamusega koosk&otilde;las v&otilde;i kui komitee ei ole arvamust esitanud, esitab komisjon v&otilde;etavate meetmete kohta viivitamata ettepaneku n&otilde;ukogule. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council shall act by a qualified majority. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu teeb otsuse kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega. </eesti>
<inglise> (c) If, within three months of the proposal being submitted to it, the Council has not acted, the proposed measures shall be adopted by the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> c) Kui n&otilde;ukogu ei ole otsust teinud kolme kuu jooksul alates ettepaneku tegemisest, v&otilde;tab komisjon ettepandud meetmed vastu. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of Article 3 shall apply for eighteen months from the date on which a matter was first referred to the Committee either under Article 3 (1) or under any other corresponding provision. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 3 s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse kaheksateistk&uuml;mne kuu jooksul alates k&uuml;simuse komiteele suunamise kuup&auml;evast vastavalt artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 1 v&otilde;i m&otilde;nele muule vastavale s&auml;ttele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall, within a period of one year following notification thereof, bring into force by law, regulation or administrative action the provisions necessary to comply with this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igus- ja haldusnormid &uuml;he aasta jooksul alates k&auml;esoleva direktiivi teatavakstegemisest. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
